  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesized that sympatholytic effect of epidural analgesia would
      attenuate the hemodynamic instability and decrease in the splanchnic blood flow caused by
      pneumoperitoneum during laparoscopic surgery. This study is to compare the effect of epidural
      analgesia and intravenous analgesia on postoperative bowel movement in patients undergoing
      laparoscopic gastrectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
